{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Surface the ref + source controls on the CLI and MCP tool schemas\n\n## Why\n\nThe new `ref` + `source` controls must be reachable by both human (CLI) and agent (MCP)\nclients, so a distributed team can target the exact code version a gate runs against.\n\n## What\n\n- Add `--ref <branch|tag|sha>` (default `origin/main`) and `--source {attested|local}` to the\n  code-reading surfaces, with the CLI<->MCP mapping pinned explicitly (no \"surfaces as they\n  exist\"):\n  - MCP tools: `review_plan`, `verify_completion`, `review_ticket`, `review_code`, `scan_spec`.\n  - CLI counterparts (the same five operations as exposed by the CLI); enumerate the exact\n    command names in the implementation and keep the two surfaces in lockstep (resolve the\n    review/review_plan and code-review/review_code naming so coverage matches one-to-one).\n- Document defaults + surface `verified_at_sha` in attested results (outputSchema/text).\n- Decouple the verified-code path from the MCP server's cwd/branch; document that `REBAR_ROOT`\n  only locates the object DB to fetch from.\n- **Validation / failure paths** (not just happy path): an unresolvable or absent `ref`, an\n  invalid `--source` value, and an unreachable/missing object DB at `REBAR_ROOT` each produce\n  a clear, actionable error (attested fails closed; cf. S1 descriptive fetch/auth errors).\n- **De-risk by vertical slice:** land ONE CLI command + ONE MCP tool end-to-end first\n  (default `origin/main` resolve + attested `verified_at_sha` + `local`=unsigned) before\n  fanning the two controls out across all five surfaces.\n\n## Scope\n\n- In: CLI flags, MCP tool-schema args, the pinned CLI<->MCP mapping, default wiring, failure/\n  validation handling, surfacing `verified_at_sha`, the vertical-slice-first sequencing.\n- Out: the underlying behavior (S1-S4); prose docs (S6).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Every code-reading CLI command AND its MCP tool counterpart accept `--ref`/`ref` and\n      `--source`/`source` with documented defaults; the CLI<->MCP mapping covers the same five\n      operations one-to-one (no naming-drift coverage gap).\n- [ ] Omitting `--ref` resolves `origin/main` -> SHA (attested) and still signs (pin recorded);\n      `--source=local` is reachable from both surfaces and reflected as unsigned in the result.\n- [ ] Attested results surface `verified_at_sha`.\n- [ ] An unresolvable/absent ref, an invalid `--source` value, and an unreachable object DB at\n      `REBAR_ROOT` each return a clear actionable error (attested fails closed) — covered by tests.\n- [ ] An AC verifies the cwd/branch decoupling: the verified-code path does not depend on the\n      MCP server's checked-out branch; `REBAR_ROOT` only locates the object DB.\n- [ ] A thin vertical slice (one CLI cmd + one MCP tool, end-to-end) lands before the full fan-out.\n\n## Additional notes + Acceptance Criteria (advisory remediation)\n\n- Pinned CLI<->MCP names (mirror the MCP tool names, confirm against the command registry):\n  `review-plan`<->`review_plan`, `verify-completion`<->`verify_completion`,\n  `review-ticket`<->`review_ticket`, `review-code`<->`review_code`, `scan-spec`<->`scan_spec`.\n- `--source` default is `attested` (stated explicitly); `--ref` default is `origin/main`.\n- The cross-surface contract (one-to-one CLI<->MCP mapping) and the cwd/branch decoupling\n  (`REBAR_ROOT` only locates the object DB) are captured in the architecture ADR (S2/S4), so\n  future maintainers don't re-couple the verified-code path to the server's checkout.\n- Error recovery: each actionable error names the remedy target — an unresolvable/absent ref\n  -> how to name a valid ref; an invalid `--source` -> the allowed enum; an unreachable\n  `REBAR_ROOT`/object DB or missing credentials -> the setup-docs section (S6).\n\n- [ ] The five CLI commands and five MCP tools are the pinned one-to-one set above (no\n      naming-drift gap); `--source` defaults to `attested`, `--ref` to `origin/main`.\n- [ ] Each failure-path error names its recovery target (valid-ref guidance / allowed --source\n      enum / REBAR_ROOT+credentials docs), consistent across both surfaces.\n- [ ] The cwd/branch decoupling + CLI<->MCP mapping are recorded in the architecture ADR."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782529652984168001,"uuid":"1fa994f8-4f03-4f75-a264-69283b8a6efc"}